name: feature-architect
version: 1.0.0
description: >
  Feature Architect — AI Staff Engineer that thinks before coding. Turns feature requests
  into production-ready implementation blueprints before a single line of code is written.
  Analyses the existing codebase, maps blast radius, designs architecture, surfaces risks,
  and produces a sequenced step-by-step implementation roadmap.

trigger_phrases:
  - "I want to add [feature]"
  - "how do I implement X"
  - "plan this feature for me"
  - "architect this for my project"
  - "what would it take to add Y"
  - "design the system for Z"
  - "give me an implementation plan"
  - "what files would change if I add X"
  - "help me plan this before I code it"
  - "[GitHub repo URL] + feature request"
  - "add X to my project"
  - "how do I build [payments / auth / notifications / search / uploads / real-time]"

entry_point: SKILL.md

files:
  - path: SKILL.md
    role: core
    description: Full 6-phase pipeline logic — Project Scan, Impact Mapping, Architecture, Risk Detection, Blueprint, Code Generation

  - path: README.md
    role: documentation
    description: User-facing overview, example output, usage instructions, and feature categories supported

  - path: references/risk-patterns.md
    role: reference
    description: >
      Deep risk pattern library with 80+ patterns across 12 categories.
      Load during Phase 4 (Risk Detection) for Medium or higher complexity features.

  - path: references/feature-blueprints.md
    role: reference
    description: >
      Pre-built architecture blueprints for 10 common integrations: Stripe billing, OAuth,
      RBAC, WebSockets, Teams/Orgs, File Uploads, Email, Search, AI/LLM, Admin panels.
      Load during Phase 3 (Architecture) and Phase 5 (Blueprint).

pipeline:
  phases:
    - id: 1
      name: Project Scan
      description: Fetch and analyse the existing codebase via GitHub API or pasted code. Build the Project Context Map (PCM).
    - id: 2
      name: Impact Mapping
      description: Determine blast radius — every file, table, API, and service the feature touches.
    - id: 3
      name: Architecture Design
      description: Design the feature end-to-end, tailored to the actual project stack and patterns.
      load_reference: references/feature-blueprints.md
    - id: 4
      name: Risk Detection
      description: Surface hidden problems before coding starts. Severity-rated risks with mitigations.
      load_reference: references/risk-patterns.md
    - id: 5
      name: Implementation Blueprint
      description: Numbered, dependency-ordered implementation roadmap with definitions of done.
    - id: 6
      name: Code Generation
      description: Actual code, generated only after the blueprint is confirmed. Step-ordered, no TODOs.

guardrails:
  - Never hallucinate project structure — only reference files that were actually read
  - Always sequence steps by dependency order
  - Prefer existing project patterns over introducing new ones
  - Flag all breaking changes to existing APIs, schemas, or auth explicitly
  - Never produce generic tutorials — every output must be project-specific

references:
  - name: Martin Fowler — Patterns of Enterprise Application Architecture
    url: https://martinfowler.com/books/eaa.html
  - name: Stripe Integration Best Practices
    url: https://stripe.com/docs/best-practices
  - name: System Design Primer
    url: https://github.com/donnemartin/system-design-primer
  - name: The Twelve-Factor App
    url: https://12factor.net/
  - name: OWASP Top 10
    url: https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/

author: Claude Skills Portfolio
tags:
  - architecture
  - planning
  - feature-design
  - risk-detection
  - staff-engineer
  - system-design
